[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'hellais', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2020-10-23 06:04:15+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'To empower community participation in censorship measurement research, we will facilitate censorship measurement workshops for human rights defenders, lawyers, journalists, policy researchers, and advocates. \r\n\r\nThe aim of these workshops is to introduce these communities to OONI‚Äôs methodologies so that they can help with more stable, diverse, and long-term deployments, as well as with relevant research and advocacy efforts based on OONI data. The workshops would discuss best practices when creating and maintaining test lists, the exact nature of tests and what insight they can provide, and how to use OONI censorship measurement data as part of research and advocacy.', 'title': '3.3 Facilitate censorship measurement workshops', 'type': 'issue'}
