[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'shakyShane', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2015-02-10 13:53:43+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "The upgrade path is seamless for this project and requires no action, however before I send a PR will you be wanting the UI disabled by default, perhaps with a commented line advising people that it's there? 

Info - [http://www.wearejh.com/news/browsersync-2-0/](http://www.wearejh.com/news/browsersync-2-0/)
Option docs - [http://www.browsersync.io/docs/options](http://www.browsersync.io/docs/options)", 'title': 'Migrate to BrowserSync ^2.0.0', 'type': 'issue'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'addyosmani', 'comment_id': 73723251.0, 'datetime': '2015-02-10 15:51:38+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "Given the UI is installed by default, do you know ~ how much larger this makes the dependency tree?

I would go ahead with a PR and we'll continue local testing. Will comment back if we have further questions.

Cheers! :)", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'addyosmani', 'comment_id': 73723638.0, 'datetime': '2015-02-10 15:53:33+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': 'Fyi, appears to be a small rendering issue in your docs http://www.browsersync.io/docs/gulp/ :)', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'shakyShane', 'comment_id': 73731368.0, 'datetime': '2015-02-10 16:30:25+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': '@username_1 - dependencies are always a valid concern - true. The UI is extremely light-weight though, and were it not for `weinre`, the tree for the UI would only be a single level.

![deps](http://cl.ly/image/3m311a3s2Q2j/Screen%20Shot%202015-02-10%20at%2016.26.01.png)

That being said, I am absolutely thinking about having a BrowserSync-lite for power-users who really only want the sync/live reload. This would be trivial to implement as the entire UI, whilst bundled, is actually just a BrowserSync plugin.

Interested to hear everyones opinions :)', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'shakyShane', 'comment_id': 73735402.0, 'datetime': '2015-02-10 16:49:37+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'also, good catch with the docs rendering, all fixed now :)', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'sindresorhus', 'comment_id': 73850992.0, 'datetime': '2015-02-11 09:05:09+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': 'Many tools go with a `module-core` for the core functionality and `module` for everything. I could see the use for `browsersync-core` and `browsersync` (which depends on `browsersync-core`).', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'addyosmani', 'comment_id': 73863761.0, 'datetime': '2015-02-11 10:56:54+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_1', 'text': "From my testing the UI is available, but isn't loaded to the end-user by default. They have to manually navigate to the URL for it in order to access, which feels okay to me.", 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'shakyShane', 'comment_id': 73864448.0, 'datetime': '2015-02-11 11:03:15+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': 'Yeah I decided against forcing it to be opened by default. For anyone wondering though, the `open` option takes any availableurl, so to open the UI instead of the default:

```
browserSync({
    server: "./app",
    open: "ui" //or `ui-external`
});
```', 'title': None, 'type': 'comment'}
